00:45:27.760 --> 00:45:31.720 align:middle line:84%
when I do something in public
space, because it's different--

00:45:31.720 --> 00:45:33.490 align:middle line:84%
People get attracted
to it, and that's

00:45:33.490 --> 00:45:36.180 align:middle line:84%
the starting point
of communication

00:45:36.180 --> 00:45:37.540 align:middle line:90%
on many different levels.

00:45:37.540 --> 00:45:39.130 align:middle line:90%
People get an experience.

00:45:39.130 --> 00:45:40.360 align:middle line:90%
They feel something.

00:45:40.360 --> 00:45:42.990 align:middle line:84%
They may feel some kind of
significance in the situation,

00:45:42.990 --> 00:45:49.390 align:middle line:84%
and you start talking together,
and you exchange experiences.

00:45:49.390 --> 00:45:51.027 align:middle line:84%
And that's what
art is all about.

00:45:51.027 --> 00:45:52.610 align:middle line:84%
That's what architecture
is all about.

00:45:52.610 --> 00:45:55.710 align:middle line:90%
That's what design is all about.

00:45:55.710 --> 00:45:58.260 align:middle line:84%
And I think if you
could just move things

00:45:58.260 --> 00:45:59.960 align:middle line:84%
a little bit in
another direction

00:45:59.960 --> 00:46:03.390 align:middle line:84%
and make new things
happen, then I

00:46:03.390 --> 00:46:06.258 align:middle line:84%
think your mission is
sort of accomplished.

00:46:06.258 --> 00:46:12.740 align:middle line:90%


00:46:12.740 --> 00:46:16.220 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, shelter is the
most basic human need.

00:46:16.220 --> 00:46:24.270 align:middle line:90%


00:46:24.270 --> 00:46:29.040 align:middle line:84%
A sleeping bag dress
is a kimono-type dress

00:46:29.040 --> 00:46:34.560 align:middle line:84%
that, when inflated, it changes
into a cylinder or cocoon

00:46:34.560 --> 00:46:36.480 align:middle line:90%
in which a person can sleep.

00:46:36.480 --> 00:46:47.230 align:middle line:90%


00:46:47.230 --> 00:46:50.600 align:middle line:84%
It comes very much from
my personal experiences.

00:46:50.600 --> 00:46:54.080 align:middle line:84%
Moving from different
countries, moving

00:46:54.080 --> 00:46:56.080 align:middle line:84%
through different
languages sort of

00:46:56.080 --> 00:47:00.380 align:middle line:84%
brought up a lot of
questions about belonging.

00:47:00.380 --> 00:47:01.340 align:middle line:90%
Where is my home?

00:47:01.340 --> 00:47:05.759 align:middle line:90%


00:47:05.759 --> 00:47:10.090 align:middle line:84%
I have a solar panel
incorporated into it

00:47:10.090 --> 00:47:11.800 align:middle line:90%
and a small computer fan.

00:47:11.800 --> 00:47:14.020 align:middle line:84%
So the solar panel
charges the battery,

00:47:14.020 --> 00:47:16.892 align:middle line:84%
and computer fan operates
off the batteries.

00:47:16.892 --> 00:47:25.460 align:middle line:90%


00:47:25.460 --> 00:47:28.580 align:middle line:84%
Experimentation
was always there--

00:47:28.580 --> 00:47:32.660 align:middle line:84%
The idea of belonging,
the idea of shelter,

00:47:32.660 --> 00:47:35.780 align:middle line:84%
the idea of space where
we feel comfortable.

00:47:35.780 --> 00:47:40.570 align:middle line:90%


00:47:40.570 --> 00:47:44.230 align:middle line:84%
But that mobility that
this process creates,

00:47:44.230 --> 00:47:45.790 align:middle line:90%
I think what I was after--

00:47:45.790 --> 00:47:48.130 align:middle line:84%
To capture this
moment in the sense

00:47:48.130 --> 00:47:55.150 align:middle line:84%
in between, because
since I left Poland,

00:47:55.150 --> 00:47:57.670 align:middle line:84%
it's always been
being in between.

00:47:57.670 --> 00:48:02.140 align:middle line:90%


00:48:02.140 --> 00:48:05.920 align:middle line:84%
Today we are more free
in terms of moving

00:48:05.920 --> 00:48:07.855 align:middle line:84%
through those
boundaries than before.

00:48:07.855 --> 00:48:16.160 align:middle line:90%


00:48:16.160 --> 00:48:18.800 align:middle line:84%
I think traveling
really is the best

00:48:18.800 --> 00:48:26.620 align:middle line:84%
way of opening an
eye to differences,

00:48:26.620 --> 00:48:28.450 align:middle line:84%
and then hopefully,
also, become more

00:48:28.450 --> 00:48:30.370 align:middle line:90%
tolerant to the differences.

00:48:30.370 --> 00:48:38.710 align:middle line:90%


00:48:38.710 --> 00:48:41.530 align:middle line:84%
I was very much
interested in the idea

00:48:41.530 --> 00:48:51.490 align:middle line:84%
of nomadism, which denies that
idea of homeland sort of as

00:48:51.490 --> 00:48:52.810 align:middle line:90%
a place of belonging.

00:48:52.810 --> 00:49:01.470 align:middle line:90%


00:49:01.470 --> 00:49:04.650 align:middle line:84%
I believe that the
modern nomad is

00:49:04.650 --> 00:49:11.580 align:middle line:84%
a person that doesn't get stuck
in a particular structure.

00:49:11.580 --> 00:49:14.520 align:middle line:84%
With that comes a
certain open-mindedness.

00:49:14.520 --> 00:49:37.850 align:middle line:90%


00:49:37.850 --> 00:49:42.320 align:middle line:84%
To feel connected, we
don't need that much space.

00:49:42.320 --> 00:49:44.600 align:middle line:90%
Maybe it's by contrast.

00:49:44.600 --> 00:49:48.640 align:middle line:84%
I think the idea of
being close to the body,

00:49:48.640 --> 00:49:50.690 align:middle line:84%
it's sort of related,
also, to the question--

00:49:50.690 --> 00:49:53.730 align:middle line:90%
Well, how much do you need?

00:49:53.730 --> 00:49:56.090 align:middle line:84%
How much, also,
comfort do you need?

00:49:56.090 --> 00:50:14.550 align:middle line:90%


00:50:14.550 --> 00:50:17.640 align:middle line:84%
So you are protected,
you are kind of isolated,

00:50:17.640 --> 00:50:21.429 align:middle line:84%
but at the same time, you
are part of the environment.

00:50:21.429 --> 00:50:26.480 align:middle line:90%


00:50:26.480 --> 00:50:29.120 align:middle line:84%
My expression presents
the idea of home

00:50:29.120 --> 00:50:31.160 align:middle line:90%
that is basically anywhere.

00:50:31.160 --> 00:50:32.450 align:middle line:90%
Home is where you are.

00:50:32.450 --> 00:50:38.860 align:middle line:90%


00:50:38.860 --> 00:50:44.950 align:middle line:84%
I still share the
'60s fascination

00:50:44.950 --> 00:50:49.480 align:middle line:84%
with technology, and
a belief in technology

00:50:49.480 --> 00:50:52.450 align:middle line:90%
and in bettering the world.

00:50:52.450 --> 00:50:59.720 align:middle line:90%


00:50:59.720 --> 00:51:03.650 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the technology showed
alternative possibilities

00:51:03.650 --> 00:51:06.600 align:middle line:90%
of living.

00:51:06.600 --> 00:51:10.530 align:middle line:84%
And perhaps people
can imagine that there

00:51:10.530 --> 00:51:14.090 align:middle line:84%
are different possibilities
to what they are used to.

00:51:14.090 --> 00:51:16.730 align:middle line:90%


00:51:16.730 --> 00:51:22.760 align:middle line:84%
That opens this flexibility
of imagination, including

00:51:22.760 --> 00:51:24.500 align:middle line:90%
how we perceive the world.

00:51:24.500 --> 00:51:28.400 align:middle line:90%


